Sentencas: Nowadays, semiconductor ionic materials have drawn significant attention for developing new electrolytes in low temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Electrical properties of Ni-doped Sm2O3 electrolyte

Sentencas: Here we investigate the effect of nickel doping on ionic conductivity of Sm2O3 as an electrolyte material for low temperature SOFCs.
Titulo: Electrical properties of Ni-doped Sm2O3 electrolyte

Sentencas: The amount of Ni ion doping has an intense effect on the electrochemical properties and power generation.
Titulo: Electrical properties of Ni-doped Sm2O3 electrolyte

Sentencas: An optimized composition of 10 mol% nickel doped samarium oxide (10NSO) as an electrolyte in the fuel cell has a high open circuit voltage (OCV) of 1.09 V and a notable power output of 1080 mW cm(-2) at 520 degrees C. Further investigation revealed that the 10NSO displays a superior ionic conduction up to 0.26 S cm(-1) at 520 degrees C. Moreover, the cell demonstrates high stability up to 80 h. The high electrochemical property and good stability recommend that the NSO is a favorable candidate for symmetrical SOFC electrolyte.
